## vnet-peering ##

azure supports 2 types of network peering
1. VNET-Peering
2. Global-Network-Peering

Vnet peering:
- enables to conect 2/more virtual network in the azure cloud
- uses microsoft backbone infrastructure to share traffic so no latency and high benefit connection.


NAT gateway -> Network address translation
  - has a public ip, all the traffic are routed to NAT gateway.
  - 

Bastion Host
  - basically a VM managed by microsoft, helps to connect to VMs with browser,a fully managed PaaS service
  - will be inside our network
  - has its own subnet, NSG
  - all the traffic will be routed to Bastion host
  - no generic ports are open
